Peru Stocks: Alturas, Cerro Verde, Credicorp, Minsur, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-05-10T18:43:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/peru-stocks-alturas-cerro-verde-credicorp-minsur-volcan.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 2:38 p.m. New York time.  The  Lima  General Index fell 2.2 percent to 21,123.01.  Mining stocks dropped on investor concern over the outcome
of the June 5 presidential elections, said Walter Bayly, chief
operating officer of  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)   Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of
Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., fell 5.5 percent to $42.50.
 Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, dropped 10.5 percent to 17 cents.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1) 
(MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin producer, fell 4.9
percent to 3.90 soles after tin declined in  London . Cia. Minera
Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based zinc and lead
producer, slid 4.1 percent to 1.18 soles. Volcan Cia Minera SAA
(VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc producer, fell 3.9 percent to
3.18 soles.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial services
company, rose 3 percent to $103 after first-quarter net income
increased 41 percent to $175 million, beating analysts’
estimates.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
